
Overview of noun grievance

The noun grievance has 3 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (1) grudge, score, grievance -- (a resentment strong enough to justify retaliation; "holding a grudge"; "settling a score")
2. (1) grievance -- (an allegation that something imposes an illegal obligation or denies some legal right or causes injustice)
3. (1) grievance -- (a complaint about a (real or imaginary) wrong that causes resentment and is grounds for action)
